metadata.name: Sacred Heart
metadata.description:
Hear me as a woman.
Have me as your sister.
On purpled battlefield breaking day,
So I might say our victory is just beginning,
See me as change,
Say I am movement,
That I am the year,
and I am the era
of the women. 

My body is a complicated thing, a sacred, beautiful, complicated thing. Life is mysteriously revealed in the delicate folds of the flower--my passion, my love, my life. I will not be ashamed or objectified.
